{
  "text": "One possible solution could be a system that makes aggregate data available on a public display, but uses private displays for zooming in for more details about specific students. For example, a public display such as that used by Chen [CITATION_1] or Jancke, et al. [CITATION_2] could display images or data describing the entire remote class. To get more information, the instructor could use a gaze-based interface that displays details on his or her private screen mounted on the podium or \"augmented reality\" glasses.",
